2024-11-16 07:01 AM
Didn't see this post at first so I made a post too, so adding that here instead

 

 

I'd like a filter option, similar to blocking explicit songs, that blocks songs that are made with AI. This would include songs whose music and/or singing is generated by AI, as well as those whose lyrics or music is written with AI. Perhaps it would block artists who have AI songs entirely, since if they have some songs that are AI, it's likely most or all are. 

 

If you want to get fancy with it, there could be levels of filtering. Like, "block all AI content", "block songs whose audio is generated by AI", "block songs written or composed by AI", "block artists who have one or more AI generated songs", etc

 

Today in one of my daylists, there were about 6 songs that I'm fairly confident were generated by AI. One time there were several in my Discover Weekly playlist. I don't want them. I've been blocking the artists as I figure out they're AI, but it's somewhat easy for people to produce songs this way, so I'm sure there's a lot out there, or will be soon. Plus it can be tricky to tell sometimes. So far ALL of these accounts have been marked as Verified Artists.

 

 

 

 

For some context, or fyi, here are some songs I'm pretty confident are generated by AI.



The easiest way for me to tell is the singing, it has sort of an aerated sound, and of course sounds a bit distorted in places. I also look at the names, and the band info, pictures, album art. If the art or description seems AI, the song probably is too imo. Also look at if the band description mentions any people, or only the band name, or talks about them like a music reviewer might, that's very ChatGPT-esque. The lyrics can also be a bit wonky, like the lines don't really go together, or they don't quite fit the meter. 

